If you take a look at the files on [Maven Central](https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/jeasy/easy-rules/4.1.0/), you can see that there is no JAR. The artifact only consists of a pom-file and its hash and signature. `easy-rules` is just the parent project including configuration for its modules.

But if you want to use a (non-pom)-dependency, you need to use an artifact that actually contains a JAR. In your case, this could be [easy-rules-core](https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/jeasy/easy-rules-core/4.1.0/):
```xml
&lt;dependency&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;org.jeasy&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;easy-rules-core&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;version&gt;${easyrules.version}&lt;/version&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
```

This is also included in the [`Use with Maven`-section](https://github.com/j-easy/easy-rules/wiki/getting-started#use-with-maven) of the [wiki](https://github.com/j-easy/easy-rules/wiki) of the [easy-rules GitHub repository](https://github.com/j-easy/easy-rules).

